# Wireshark Network Traffic Analysis Lab

## Objective
Capture and analyze network traffic to identify protocols and potential security concerns.

## Tools Used
- Wireshark

## What I Did
- Captured live network traffic
- Filtered packets using protocol filters (TCP, DNS)
- Identified IP addresses and communication patterns

## Key Findings
- Observed DNS queries and responses
- Identified standard TCP handshake behavior
- Noted how traffic flows between devices on a network

## Skills Gained
- Packet analysis
- Understanding network protocols
- Traffic filtering techniques

## Notes
This lab helped strengthen my understanding of how real network traffic looks and how to begin analyzing it from a security perspective.
